Jochen's going on slicks.
You wanna change?

995
01:06:17,092 --> 01:06:19,572
- Is Niki gonna change?
- No.

996
01:06:19,652 --> 01:06:21,734
Then we stay on wets, too.

997
01:06:29,572 --> 01:06:31,336
- Niki, okay?
- I'm good.

998
01:06:33,812 --> 01:06:36,292
All right, fire her up.

999
01:06:49,652 --> 01:06:52,258
This season's fight for the
Formula 1 World Championship

1000
01:06:52,292 --> 01:06:55,933
has so far been the
story of two men.

1001
01:06:55,972 --> 01:06:59,613
Thus far, it's been going pretty
much the way of Niki Lauda.

1002
01:06:59,652 --> 01:07:02,337
But James Hunt has
qualified fastest here.

1003
01:07:02,452 --> 01:07:05,456
He is on pole position for
the German Grand Prix,

1004
01:07:05,532 --> 01:07:08,615
with Niki Lauda alongside
in the blood-red Ferrari.

1005
01:07:10,052 --> 01:07:11,463
It's a long race.

1006
01:07:11,532 --> 01:07:14,183
If the track starts to dry out,

1007
01:07:14,292 --> 01:07:17,136
the wet-weather tyres will
no longer be as quick.

1008
01:07:38,572 --> 01:07:40,574
Niki Lauda and James
Hunt, side by side

1009
01:07:40,652 --> 01:07:43,815
on the front row of the grid,
go away absolutely as one.

1010
01:07:58,012 --> 01:08:00,219
Lauda very aggressive
on Hunt there,

1011
01:08:00,332 --> 01:08:02,334
forcing the McLaren
onto the grass.

1012
01:08:06,692 --> 01:08:08,103
Lauda has the lead at the moment.

1013
01:08:08,172 --> 01:08:10,539
Lauda leads into the first corner.

1014
01:08:10,732 --> 01:08:12,700
Hunt is in second place.

1015
01:08:17,372 --> 01:08:19,943
Mass storming past Hunt.

1016
01:08:20,012 --> 01:08:22,697
He made the right choice to go
with the dry-weather tyres.

1017
01:08:24,212 --> 01:08:26,021
Mass passing Lauda now.

1018
01:08:26,132 --> 01:08:30,057
Jochen Mass, in the number
12 McLaren, takes the lead.

1019
01:08:30,212 --> 01:08:31,896
Jochen Mass the clear leader,

1020
01:08:32,052 --> 01:08:34,100
with everybody else
making the decision

1021
01:08:34,212 --> 01:08:36,294
to change tyres after just
one lap of this race.

1022
01:08:36,372 --> 01:08:38,579
He's coming in. Come on, let's go.

1023
01:08:46,732 --> 01:08:50,782
See? I told you to go on slicks.
You should have taken my advice.

1024
01:08:50,892 --> 01:08:52,656
Fuck off. Where's Niki?

1025
01:08:52,732 --> 01:08:55,417
Behind you. He made
the same mistake.

1026
01:09:08,172 --> 01:09:09,901
Come on.

1027
01:09:12,452 --> 01:09:14,261
Come on. What's going on?

1028
01:09:15,772 --> 01:09:17,531
The tyre-changing
frenzy has caused

1029
01:09:17,532 --> 01:09:19,094
a huge reshuffling of the pack,

1030
01:09:19,132 --> 01:09:21,041
with Jochen Mass in the lead now.

1031
01:09:21,042 --> 01:09:22,102
You're clear. Go.

1032
01:09:22,652 --> 01:09:23,778
Quick.

1033
01:09:25,252 --> 01:09:27,016
Lauda urging his
mechanics to hurry.

1034
01:09:27,092 --> 01:09:28,253
Quicker, quicker, quicker.

1035
01:09:30,012 --> 01:09:32,094
It's a disaster. Come on.

1036
01:09:43,652 --> 01:09:45,222
What's going on, you assholes?

1037
01:10:08,972 --> 01:10:11,134
This race has gone
wrong for him so far.

1038
01:10:11,212 --> 01:10:14,659
His championship rival, James
Hunt, is a long way up the road.

1039
01:10:25,532 --> 01:10:26,977
Lauda passing car after car.

1040
01:10:27,012 --> 01:10:30,494
He's just going past Mario
Andretti's Lotus there.

1041
01:11:17,212 --> 01:11:19,214
Niki.

1042
01:11:24,212 --> 01:11:26,294
Get me out. Help me.

1043
01:11:26,892 --> 01:11:29,452
We have an accident on the
course. Red flags are out.

1044
01:11:29,732 --> 01:11:31,766
Several cars are
involved. Looks like

1045
01:11:31,767 --> 01:11:33,532
it might be one of the Ferraris.

1046
01:11:40,732 --> 01:11:43,099
- Come this way.
- Come on, come on.

1047
01:11:55,332 --> 01:11:56,743
Keep trying.

1048
01:12:04,412 --> 01:12:06,052
- Come this way.
- Okay.

1049
01:12:11,780 --> 01:12:15,396
News is reaching
us that Niki Lauda

1050
01:12:15,397 --> 01:12:18,410
was involved in the accident.

1051
01:12:18,490 --> 01:12:21,309
He is being flown by helicopter to

1052
01:12:21,310 --> 01:12:24,460
Mannheim hospital
with severe burns.

1053
01:12:58,120 --> 01:13:02,200
It's not the burns to his
face that are the danger.

1054
01:13:03,080 --> 01:13:05,080
It's the burns to his lungs.

1055
01:13:07,830 --> 01:13:10,585
In the intensive care
unit, six doctors and

1056
01:13:10,586 --> 01:13:13,090
thirty-four nurses
are on duty for him.

1057
01:13:14,300 --> 01:13:17,590
But his condition is far worse
than originally feared.

1058
01:13:44,332 --> 01:13:47,779
The flood, which swept down Big
Thompson Canyon in Colorado,

1059
01:13:47,852 --> 01:13:49,536
was the worst since records began.

1060
01:13:49,572 --> 01:13:52,098
In Formula 1 today, victory
celebrations were muted

1061
01:13:52,172 --> 01:13:54,324
after a horrific
accident involving

1062
01:13:54,325 --> 01:13:55,938
world champion Niki Lauda.

1063
01:13:56,012 --> 01:13:57,935
Due to safety concerns
before the race,

1064
01:13:58,012 --> 01:14:00,379
the Austrian had said
he would not take part,

1065
01:14:00,412 --> 01:14:01,902
but in the end he did.

1066
01:14:03,292 --> 01:14:05,579
He was making up for lost time
when he went off the track,

1067
01:14:05,692 --> 01:14:08,059
puncturing the
Ferrari's fuel tank.

1068
01:14:08,452 --> 01:14:10,739
Brett Lunger was unable to
avoid the flaming wreck,

1069
01:14:10,892 --> 01:14:13,816
but was unhurt and joined with the
other drivers to rescue Lauda,

1070
01:14:13,892 --> 01:14:16,782
who was taken to Mannheim
Hospital with severe burns,

1071
01:14:16,892 --> 01:14:20,533
the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.

1072
01:14:20,652 --> 01:14:22,654
Niki Lauda was trapped
for almost a minute

1073
01:14:22,732 --> 01:14:25,383
in a searing inferno
of 800-plus degrees.

1074
01:14:34,212 --> 01:14:35,867
Do we have any
change this morning?

1075
01:14:35,868 --> 01:14:36,868
No...

1076
01:14:36,869 --> 01:14:38,415
Frau Lauda. Frau Lauda?

1077
01:14:39,300 --> 01:14:41,470
He's awake and just spoke.

1078
01:14:43,010 --> 01:14:46,600
He said, "Tell the priest to
fuck off. I'm still alive."

1079
01:14:46,770 --> 01:14:48,430
You can go in.

1080
01:16:10,180 --> 01:16:14,770
James Hunt gains on the
absent Niki Lauda.

1081
01:16:21,940 --> 01:16:24,780
We need to vacuum the lungs.

1082
01:16:25,160 --> 01:16:27,570
I should warn you.
It won't be easy.

1083
01:17:36,560 --> 01:17:37,940
Do it again.

1084
01:17:38,190 --> 01:17:42,320
Are you sure? The lungs
will already be bruised.

1085
01:18:24,270 --> 01:18:26,360
Please, stop.

1086
01:18:27,360 --> 01:18:30,910
I know what you're
thinking, but please...

1087
01:18:32,240 --> 01:18:35,540
If you love me, you
won't say a word.

1088
01:19:12,172 --> 01:19:14,061
- Morning, chaps.
- Hey, here's the man.

1089
01:19:14,252 --> 01:19:15,902
Looking good.

1090
01:19:19,132 --> 01:19:21,942
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

1091
01:19:22,012 --> 01:19:24,060
- What about him?
- He's here.

1092
01:19:24,372 --> 01:19:25,897
- What?
- He's racing.

1093
01:19:41,252 --> 01:19:42,902
Niki.

1094
01:19:49,532 --> 01:19:51,057
It's that bad, huh?

1095
01:19:52,372 --> 01:19:53,783
No.

1096
01:19:54,652 --> 01:19:57,576
In hospital I asked them
straight, no bullshit,

1097
01:19:57,652 --> 01:19:59,495
how bad my appearance would be.

1098
01:20:00,732 --> 01:20:03,099
They said with time
it would be fine.

1099
01:20:03,972 --> 01:20:05,576
But it won't.

1100
01:20:06,492 --> 01:20:09,336
I can tell, seeing your reaction.

1101
01:20:10,292 --> 01:20:13,296
I will spend the rest of my life
with a face that frightens people.

1102
01:20:17,412 --> 01:20:19,321
You know, Niki, I
tried to write you

1103
01:20:19,322 --> 01:20:21,178
a letter at the
time, to apologise.

1104
01:20:22,812 --> 01:20:25,292
The drivers' meeting in
Germany, before the race.

1105
01:20:25,412 --> 01:20:27,938
- I swayed the room.
- Yes, you did.

1106
01:20:28,132 --> 01:20:30,339
That race should never
have gone ahead.

1107
01:20:31,092 --> 01:20:32,696
No, it shouldn't.

1108
01:20:33,132 --> 01:20:35,270
So, in many ways, I
feel responsible

1109
01:20:35,271 --> 01:20:36,773
for what happened, and...

1110
01:20:36,852 --> 01:20:38,422
You were.

1111
01:20:40,092 --> 01:20:41,821
But, trust me...

1112
01:20:42,972 --> 01:20:47,022
watching you win those races while
I was fighting for my life...

1113
01:20:49,332 --> 01:20:52,541
you were equally responsible for
getting me back in the car.

1114
01:21:20,292 --> 01:21:22,977
- How are you feeling, Niki?
- Fine.

1115
01:21:23,372 --> 01:21:25,401
Niki, can you confirm
to us exactly

1116
01:21:25,402 --> 01:21:26,979
which procedures you've had

1117
01:21:27,012 --> 01:21:29,014
and the expectations
for your recovery?

1118
01:21:29,572 --> 01:21:31,017
Sure.

1119
01:21:31,172 --> 01:21:32,981
I had a skin graft operation,

1120
01:21:33,012 --> 01:21:35,333
where they put half my
right thigh in my face.

1121
01:21:37,532 --> 01:21:42,333
Now, it doesn't look too good,
but one unexpected advantage is

1122
01:21:42,372 --> 01:21:44,659
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft,

1123
01:21:44,732 --> 01:21:46,463
so sweat will never
run into my eyes

1124
01:21:46,464 --> 01:21:48,100
again, which is good for a driver.

1125
01:21:50,372 --> 01:21:52,022
When they heard about
your condition,

1126
01:21:52,052 --> 01:21:53,462
Ferrari immediately hired a

1127
01:21:53,463 --> 01:21:55,499
replacement driver,
Carlos Reutemann.

1128
01:21:56,172 --> 01:22:00,177
Yeah, before even
reaching the hospital.

1129
01:22:00,212 --> 01:22:02,260
Is Reutemann driving today, too?

1130
01:22:02,692 --> 01:22:05,696
Yes, and keen to
make an impression.

1131
01:22:05,892 --> 01:22:09,863
So, let's see where Mr Reutemann
finishes and where I finish today.

1132
01:22:11,412 --> 01:22:14,097
James Hunt and McLaren have caught
up a lot while you were away.

1133
01:22:14,732 --> 01:22:16,222
Yes.

1134
01:22:16,852 --> 01:22:19,776
So is there a question now, or are
you just trying to piss me off?

1135
01:22:23,132 --> 01:22:24,861
You still think you can win?

1136
01:22:25,292 --> 01:22:27,056
Yes, of course.

1137
01:22:27,092 --> 01:22:29,094
I have the better car.

1138
01:22:29,212 --> 01:22:31,692
And possibly I'm
the better driver.

1139
01:22:31,892 --> 01:22:34,293
But he's a clever guy, and
he's used his time well

1140
01:22:34,372 --> 01:22:38,422
while I was lying half-dead in
hospital to win some points.

1141
01:22:40,372 --> 01:22:43,057
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1142
01:22:49,252 --> 01:22:52,734
She said, Sweetie, you don't
need a face to drive.

1143
01:22:52,812 --> 01:22:54,940
You just need a right foot.

1144
01:22:55,252 --> 01:22:57,619
I'm being serious.

1145
01:22:57,812 --> 01:23:00,146
Do you really think
your marriage can

1146
01:23:00,147 --> 01:23:02,295
survive with the way you look now?

1147
01:23:04,932 --> 01:23:06,980
And I'm being serious, too.

1148
01:23:07,972 --> 01:23:10,942
Fuck you. Press conference over.

1149
01:23:16,132 --> 01:23:18,052
- That was hairy.
- Well, you got noticed, Clive.

1150
01:23:18,072 --> 01:23:19,258
I'll tell you that.

1151
01:23:19,332 --> 01:23:20,936
I thought it went
well, to be honest.

1152
01:23:21,012 --> 01:23:22,932
They don't like it when
it's not going their way.

1153
01:23:22,952 --> 01:23:24,496
- Clive.
- That's the game.

1154
01:23:24,612 --> 01:23:26,853
- See you.
- See you later.

1155
01:23:26,932 --> 01:23:28,821
- James, are you all right?
- Good, yeah.

1156
01:23:28,932 --> 01:23:30,616
Listen, I think I've
got something for you

1157
01:23:30,692 --> 01:23:32,456
on that last question, about Niki.

1158
01:23:32,492 --> 01:23:35,098
- You heard about that?
- I did.

1159
01:23:36,332 --> 01:23:38,061
James.

1160
01:23:44,292 --> 01:23:46,863
Please, James...

1161
01:23:47,852 --> 01:23:50,776
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1162
01:23:53,212 --> 01:23:54,623
Prick.

1163
01:24:11,492 --> 01:24:13,998
So Niki Lauda, just
42 days after his

1164
01:24:13,999 --> 01:24:16,373
near-fatal accident
at Nurburgring,

1165
01:24:16,492 --> 01:24:17,982
will race here today at Monza

1166
01:24:18,052 --> 01:24:21,818
against all medical advice and
no doubt in incredible pain.

1167
01:24:54,532 --> 01:24:56,182
Niki Lauda.

1168
01:25:04,892 --> 01:25:07,293
Photographers, please
clear the grid.

1169
01:25:07,532 --> 01:25:09,694
Niki, it's time.

1170
01:25:11,212 --> 01:25:12,702
Okay?

1171
01:25:19,372 --> 01:25:20,783
Please clear the grid.

1172
01:25:23,412 --> 01:25:25,540
One minute to go.

1173
01:26:02,860 --> 01:26:06,570
That's a bad start for
Lauda, he's slow away.

1174
01:26:11,332 --> 01:26:14,176
The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.

1175
01:26:14,252 --> 01:26:16,698
He's being overtaken
by car after car.

1176
01:26:19,580 --> 01:26:21,249
A terrible start for the Austrian.

1177
01:26:21,250 --> 01:26:23,590
It's perhaps too soon for
him to be racing again.

1178
01:26:26,492 --> 01:26:29,621
Lauda's off line. He runs
wide onto the grass.

1179
01:26:34,452 --> 01:26:36,136
He wrestles it back
onto the track,

1180
01:26:36,332 --> 01:26:39,142
but that was a bad
moment for Niki.

1181
01:26:43,012 --> 01:26:45,219
Niki Lauda's the
reigning world champion,

1182
01:26:45,292 --> 01:26:48,501
but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there,

1183
01:26:48,652 --> 01:26:51,462
to himself and to the
rest of the field.

1184
01:26:53,452 --> 01:26:57,343
And Stuck has collided with
Mario Andretti's Lotus.

1185
01:26:57,492 --> 01:27:00,655
Niki's boxed in. He's
got nowhere to go.

1186
01:27:15,092 --> 01:27:18,653
Niki Lauda is actually making a
move. He's on Brambilla's tail.

1187
01:27:21,932 --> 01:27:24,583
He pulls out of the
slipstream to overtake.

1188
01:27:25,332 --> 01:27:27,653
Lauda's starting to find the form

1189
01:27:27,772 --> 01:27:29,740
that, early in this race,
we believed he'd lost.

1190
01:27:36,172 --> 01:27:38,007
Lauda's now lapping faster than

1191
01:27:38,008 --> 01:27:40,257
Reutemann and closing
the gap ahead.

1192
01:27:44,172 --> 01:27:46,743
Lauda closing on Carlos Reutemann,

1193
01:27:46,852 --> 01:27:50,015
the man called in to be his
replacement in the Ferrari team.

1194
01:27:59,052 --> 01:28:00,861
And there's James Hunt's McLaren,

1195
01:28:00,972 --> 01:28:03,418
smoking stationary by
the side of the road.

1196
01:28:07,052 --> 01:28:10,135
This is bad news for
Hunt's championship hopes.

1197
01:28:14,532 --> 01:28:15,943
It's Ronnie Peterson

1198
01:28:16,052 --> 01:28:18,419
who comes home the
winner here at Monza.

1199
01:28:18,612 --> 01:28:21,502
But all eyes are on the man who
finishes a brilliant fourth,

1200
01:28:22,452 --> 01:28:24,580
Niki Lauda.

1201
01:29:05,452 --> 01:29:07,773
What a race, what a
man, what a season.

1202
01:29:07,852 --> 01:29:10,014
With a fourth-place finish
and three priceless points,

1203
01:29:10,092 --> 01:29:12,094
it means that Niki Lauda
is a major step closer

1204
01:29:12,132 --> 01:29:14,339
to retaining the
World Championship.

1205
01:30:13,492 --> 01:30:17,019
So, the long, gruelling and
incredibly dramatic season

1206
01:30:17,052 --> 01:30:19,419
comes down to this
final race in Japan

1207
01:30:19,492 --> 01:30:22,018
in the shadow of Mount Fuji.

1208
01:30:22,092 --> 01:30:23,537
Niki Lauda goes into

1209
01:30:23,572 --> 01:30:25,017
this deciding race at Fuji

1210
01:30:25,092 --> 01:30:27,254
just three points
ahead of James Hunt.

1211
01:30:27,332 --> 01:30:29,592
Hunt knowing he must
beat the Austrian

1212
01:30:29,593 --> 01:30:31,621
fair and square to take the title.

1213
01:30:33,172 --> 01:30:36,699
James, do you think you can
cope with the pressure?

1214
01:30:36,732 --> 01:30:40,259
Well, I've never really understood
what that means. I love my job.

1215
01:30:40,372 --> 01:30:42,420
I love competing. I love racing.

1216
01:30:42,612 --> 01:30:44,455
Maybe you should ask Niki.

1217
01:30:44,532 --> 01:30:46,853
He's the World Champion.
He's got everything to lose.

1218
01:30:46,892 --> 01:30:49,213
Mr Lauda, are you
feeling pressure?

1219
01:30:49,292 --> 01:30:51,738
Do I look like I'm
feeling pressure?

1220
01:30:53,812 --> 01:30:56,054
I am World Champion,
and on the verge

1221
01:30:56,055 --> 01:30:57,942
to become World Champion again.

1222
01:30:58,052 --> 01:31:00,054
Hunt now has the
opportunity to win,

1223
01:31:00,132 --> 01:31:02,214
but it's not so easy
to become a champion.

1224
01:31:02,292 --> 01:31:05,421
You have to really believe
it to make it possible.

1225
01:31:05,572 --> 01:31:07,620
James, is there anything
you'd like to add?

1226
01:31:07,732 --> 01:31:09,775
If Niki is being
tricky and getting a

1227
01:31:09,776 --> 01:31:11,657
kicky out of playing mind games...

1228
01:31:11,732 --> 01:31:14,099
then fine, I'm flattered.

1229
01:31:14,212 --> 01:31:17,773
But the fact is, momentum is
with me. I've never felt better.

1230
01:31:17,892 --> 01:31:20,463
And I fully expect the next
press conference we will have

1231
01:31:20,572 --> 01:31:22,734
will be with me as World Champion.

1232
01:31:24,572 --> 01:31:27,018
How will you cope with the
weather, bad conditions?

1233
01:31:27,092 --> 01:31:30,574
Intermittent heavy rain has been
forecast here at Fuji today,

1234
01:31:30,652 --> 01:31:34,134
along with strong winds
and occasional fog

1235
01:31:34,252 --> 01:31:36,141
rolling in from the mountain.

1236
01:31:37,932 --> 01:31:40,583
And so, with today's
Japanese Grand Prix to come,

1237
01:31:40,652 --> 01:31:42,416
Lauda's lead a mere three points.

1238
01:31:42,492 --> 01:31:44,176
What a way to finish the season.

1239
01:31:44,772 --> 01:31:46,262
Hunt or Lauda?

1240
01:31:46,332 --> 01:31:47,774
Well, the final
chapter will unfold

1241
01:31:47,775 --> 01:31:49,336
when we bring you
extended coverage...

1242
01:31:49,452 --> 01:31:52,501
They've got to cancel the
race. It's lethal out there.

1243
01:31:52,572 --> 01:31:54,700
The race is going ahead.

1244
01:31:54,772 --> 01:31:56,892
Television rights have been
sold all around the world.

1245
01:31:56,912 --> 01:31:59,343
The showdown between you and
Niki is all anyone wants to see.

1246
01:31:59,412 --> 01:32:02,814
With heavy rain continuing
to fall here at Fuji,

1247
01:32:02,892 --> 01:32:04,974
a decision has finally been made.

1248
01:32:05,092 --> 01:32:09,017
The 1976 Japanese Grand
Prix will go ahead.

1249
01:32:09,092 --> 01:32:11,777
All drivers to your cars, please.

1250
01:32:36,412 --> 01:32:37,823
Five minutes to go.

1251
01:33:21,012 --> 01:33:22,457
- All right?
- All right.

1252
01:33:22,532 --> 01:33:24,853
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1253
01:33:24,932 --> 01:33:26,661
To let the condensation out.

1254
01:33:26,732 --> 01:33:29,463
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1255
01:33:29,532 --> 01:33:31,899
Trust me, this race is
all about the start.

1256
01:33:33,812 --> 01:33:36,383
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah, hold it, Teddy.

1257
01:33:50,852 --> 01:33:52,502
Okay, start the bastard.

1258
01:33:55,492 --> 01:33:57,142
Good luck, kid.

1259
01:33:58,532 --> 01:33:59,943
Good luck, James.

1260
01:34:39,492 --> 01:34:41,494
Thirty seconds to go.

1261
01:35:00,932 --> 01:35:03,094
Electric tension here at Fuji.

1262
01:35:03,172 --> 01:35:05,727
80,000 bedraggled
race fans and the

1263
01:35:05,728 --> 01:35:08,212
racing grudge match of the decade.

1264
01:35:08,292 --> 01:35:10,420
And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position,

1265
01:35:10,492 --> 01:35:12,494
James Hunt alongside him.

1266
01:35:14,652 --> 01:35:16,575
On Row 2 of the grid,

1267
01:35:16,652 --> 01:35:18,541
there is Niki Lauda,

1268
01:35:18,612 --> 01:35:21,058
and on Row 3 of the grid, Jody
Scheckter from South Africa

1269
01:35:21,132 --> 01:35:22,577
in the six-wheel Tyrrell.

1270
01:35:22,652 --> 01:35:24,734
Behind him, the rest
of the 25-car field.

1271
01:35:42,572 --> 01:35:46,577
There's the flag, and finally the
Japanese Grand Prix is underway.

1272
01:35:58,812 --> 01:36:01,975
In these conditions, it must
be almost impossible to drive

1273
01:36:02,052 --> 01:36:04,054
a 450-horsepower car.

1274
01:36:31,212 --> 01:36:34,216
And it's Andretti who has the
lead, but Hunt is attacking.

1275
01:36:34,292 --> 01:36:37,262
Hunt's going round the
outside of Andretti.

1276
01:36:37,332 --> 01:36:38,902
Niki Lauda following him through.

1277
01:36:38,972 --> 01:36:41,737
Hunt leads into the
first right-hander.

1278
01:37:24,812 --> 01:37:26,572
Hunt comes through to
complete his first lap,

1279
01:37:26,612 --> 01:37:28,023
leading the field.

1280
01:37:28,092 --> 01:37:30,220
At least he has clear
vision in front of him.

1281
01:37:30,332 --> 01:37:32,494
Niki Lauda, behind
him, eating his spray.

1282
01:37:51,972 --> 01:37:53,383
Lauda is slowing.

1283
01:37:53,452 --> 01:37:56,342
Niki Lauda is bringing the
Ferrari number one into the pit.

1284
01:37:58,092 --> 01:37:59,529
Some sort of problem, we can't

1285
01:37:59,530 --> 01:38:01,301
imagine what, so
early in the race.

1286
01:38:07,612 --> 01:38:11,059
What's wrong with the car?
What's wrong with the car?

1287
01:38:12,212 --> 01:38:13,941
Niki, what's wrong with the car?

1288
01:38:14,292 --> 01:38:16,374
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1289
01:38:20,772 --> 01:38:23,139
- What are you doing?
- I'm stopping.

1290
01:38:23,212 --> 01:38:25,374
His mechanics are asking
what the problem is.

1291
01:38:25,452 --> 01:38:27,773
But wait. Niki Lauda's
getting out of the car.

1292
01:38:27,892 --> 01:38:29,496
This is sensational.

1293
01:38:29,572 --> 01:38:32,496
The reigning World Champion,
Niki Lauda, is out of this race.

1294
01:38:33,412 --> 01:38:35,096
It's too dangerous.

1295
01:38:35,172 --> 01:38:36,777
Niki, you want me
to say there was a

1296
01:38:36,778 --> 01:38:38,381
problem with the
car, for the media?

1297
01:38:39,692 --> 01:38:41,182
No.

1298
01:38:41,572 --> 01:38:42,983
Tell them the truth.

1299
01:38:43,852 --> 01:38:45,422
Now, what is happening?

1300
01:38:45,532 --> 01:38:47,766
They're talking to
the team manager.

1301
01:38:47,767 --> 01:38:49,457
Lauda explaining something.

1302
01:39:05,012 --> 01:39:08,300
With Lauda out, James Hunt knows
he has to finish this race

1303
01:39:08,372 --> 01:39:12,138
in third place or higher
to be World Champion.

1304
01:39:12,212 --> 01:39:14,897
But the job's not done
yet for James Hunt.

1305
01:39:14,972 --> 01:39:19,580
In these dreadful conditions, he
still has to go the distance.

1306
01:39:20,692 --> 01:39:22,535
Fifteen laps to go here at Fuji.

1307
01:39:22,652 --> 01:39:24,734
James Hunt or Niki Lauda?

1308
01:39:24,812 --> 01:39:27,895
This extraordinary
season is not over yet.

1309
01:39:27,972 --> 01:39:31,419
In this treacherous final
round, can James Hunt hang on?

1310
01:39:31,932 --> 01:39:33,775
And the scoreboard tells a story.

1311
01:39:33,852 --> 01:39:36,662
Lap 58. Hunt in the lead.

1312
01:39:38,652 --> 01:39:40,495
Oh, God, his tyres,
they're blistering.

1313
01:39:42,132 --> 01:39:43,896
Brambilla very close behind now,

1314
01:39:43,972 --> 01:39:45,940
closing on him all the time now.

1315
01:39:46,052 --> 01:39:49,215
And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.

1316
01:39:49,292 --> 01:39:51,818
Hunt cuts across the
orange March nose.

1317
01:39:51,932 --> 01:39:54,219
Hunt's not having that at
all. And he's spinning.

1318
01:39:54,292 --> 01:39:57,455
He missed Hunt there, but almost
took James Hunt out of the race

1319
01:39:57,532 --> 01:39:59,899
and out of the world championship.

1320
01:39:59,972 --> 01:40:02,703
Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.

1321
01:40:07,252 --> 01:40:09,220
Mario Andretti's going past Hunt.

1322
01:40:09,692 --> 01:40:12,696
Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a problem.

1323
01:40:18,532 --> 01:40:20,296
Despite these wet conditions,

1324
01:40:20,372 --> 01:40:22,212
these wet-weather tyres
do wear extremely fast.

1325
01:40:22,232 --> 01:40:24,360
Hunt's tyres, they've gone.

1326
01:40:24,572 --> 01:40:28,258
Hunt nursing his car
back to the pit stop.

1327
01:40:30,252 --> 01:40:32,300
That back marker's
going past Hunt.

1328
01:40:44,732 --> 01:40:47,417
Look at that left front tyre...
Right front tyre, sorry.

1329
01:40:47,492 --> 01:40:50,655
No tread on it at all. And
the other one is flat.

1330
01:40:50,812 --> 01:40:52,940
Let's go. Let's go.

1331
01:40:57,492 --> 01:40:59,893
Okay? When did you
break your gear lever?

1332
01:40:59,972 --> 01:41:01,576
Nine or ten laps ago.

1333
01:41:01,652 --> 01:41:04,098
- Alastair, we need to lift it.
- Come on.

1334
01:41:04,212 --> 01:41:05,896
- At the front.
- Let's go.

1335
01:41:05,972 --> 01:41:09,181
Regazzoni's Ferrari and
Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier

1336
01:41:09,252 --> 01:41:10,902
have gone ahead.

1337
01:41:11,012 --> 01:41:12,616
Come on, hurry.

1338
01:41:12,692 --> 01:41:15,741
You did it. You're going
to be World Champion.

1339
01:41:15,812 --> 01:41:17,257
Not yet.

1340
01:41:17,332 --> 01:41:21,098
A few laps ago, James Hunt was
looking like champion elect.

1341
01:41:21,172 --> 01:41:23,539
Now it looks as though it's
all gone wrong for him.

1342
01:41:24,972 --> 01:41:26,383
- James.
- Come on.

1343
01:41:26,452 --> 01:41:27,897
- Listen.
- What?

1344
01:41:27,972 --> 01:41:30,213
Just go easy out there.

1345
01:41:30,292 --> 01:41:34,263
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1346
01:41:34,332 --> 01:41:36,221
We want you back in one piece.

1347
01:41:36,292 --> 01:41:39,660
You're too far back. There's too
many drivers in front of you.

1348
01:41:39,732 --> 01:41:43,737
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1349
01:41:44,132 --> 01:41:45,622
Clear.

1350
01:41:45,692 --> 01:41:47,217
James.

1351
01:41:48,892 --> 01:41:50,815
- Clear.
- Fuck it.

1352
01:41:54,732 --> 01:41:57,975
James Hunt rejoins the
race in sixth position.

1353
01:41:58,052 --> 01:41:59,800
There are four laps left to go.

1354
01:41:59,801 --> 01:42:01,943
Surely no way back
for the Brit now.

1355
01:42:21,812 --> 01:42:23,052
Concentrate, Superstar.

1356
01:42:23,252 --> 01:42:24,936
Just brings it back under control.

1357
01:42:25,052 --> 01:42:26,258
Sliding the McLaren

1358
01:42:26,332 --> 01:42:27,572
on the very edge there.

1359
01:42:29,492 --> 01:42:30,778
Hunt's M23

1360
01:42:30,892 --> 01:42:32,532
twitching this way and
that under braking.

1361
01:42:32,572 --> 01:42:33,972
And he almost loses
it right there.

1362
01:42:34,092 --> 01:42:36,813
Hunt on the tail of Jacques
Lafitte in the blue Ligier.

1363
01:42:44,772 --> 01:42:46,183
Oh, don't do it, James.

1364
01:42:49,612 --> 01:42:51,182
He's inches away
from the pit wall.

1365
01:42:51,252 --> 01:42:53,061
He's inches away from the Ligier.

1366
01:43:02,092 --> 01:43:04,493
James Hunt has made
up another place,

1367
01:43:04,572 --> 01:43:05,573
but it's not enough,

1368
01:43:05,652 --> 01:43:06,892
and this race is running out.

1369
01:43:15,932 --> 01:43:17,934
And Watson has spun.
Watson has spun.

1370
01:43:22,572 --> 01:43:25,337
Hunt manages to weave his way
between that back marker

1371
01:43:25,412 --> 01:43:27,414
and the stationary Penske.

1372
01:43:27,492 --> 01:43:29,494
He's catching Regazzoni

1373
01:43:29,572 --> 01:43:31,652
but, in these conditions,
it's one thing to catch up,

1374
01:43:31,672 --> 01:43:33,879
it's quite another to overtake.

1375
01:43:36,892 --> 01:43:39,047
He's alongside Clay
Regazzoni. This

1376
01:43:39,048 --> 01:43:41,022
could be the world championship.

1377
01:43:49,452 --> 01:43:50,977
He's got him.

1378
01:43:51,430 --> 01:43:54,470
The scoreboard still
shows Hunt in 5th place.

1379
01:44:06,252 --> 01:44:08,334
Hunt crosses the line.

1380
01:44:08,412 --> 01:44:10,310
Now, he needed to
finish third to score

1381
01:44:10,311 --> 01:44:12,019
enough points to
be World Champion,

1382
01:44:12,092 --> 01:44:14,385
and in the confusion
here, we're being

1383
01:44:14,386 --> 01:44:16,620
told that he may
have finished fifth.

1384
01:44:16,692 --> 01:44:18,820
He finished fifth?

1385
01:44:18,892 --> 01:44:21,702
Our lap charts show
Hunt in third place.

1386
01:44:21,772 --> 01:44:23,695
Well, if the scoreboard's right,

1387
01:44:23,772 --> 01:44:26,298
it means he's just missed
out on the championship.

1388
01:44:26,372 --> 01:44:30,013
Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a heroic drive.

1389
01:44:33,972 --> 01:44:36,498
I can see the race
stewards conferring,

1390
01:44:36,572 --> 01:44:38,222
examining the official lap charts.

1391
01:44:38,292 --> 01:44:40,693
We're just going to have to
wait for their verdict here.

1392
01:44:58,332 --> 01:44:59,902
Let's get you out of there, buddy.

1393
01:44:59,942 --> 01:45:00,942
I'm sorry, Teddy. I'm sorry. I

1394
01:45:00,943 --> 01:45:02,139
thought I could
make up the ground.

1395
01:45:02,140 --> 01:45:04,214
Sorry? What are you talking
about? You did it.

1396
01:45:04,292 --> 01:45:07,057
- Did what?
- Jesus. You crazy bastard.

1397
01:45:07,132 --> 01:45:08,882
You came third. You
got the points.

1398
01:45:08,883 --> 01:45:10,341
You're champion of the world.

1399
01:45:10,852 --> 01:45:14,095
James Hunt is now
officially confirmed

1400
01:45:14,212 --> 01:45:16,260
as finishing third here in Japan,

1401
01:45:16,892 --> 01:45:20,533
and that means he is
champion of the world.

1402
01:45:22,012 --> 01:45:27,303
Our new World Champion, James
Hunt, by just one single point.

1403
01:45:32,492 --> 01:45:33,982
Did we really win?

1404
01:45:38,052 --> 01:45:40,293
World bloody Champion.

1405
01:45:49,092 --> 01:45:50,981
Tell us, James, what are
you going to do now?

1406
01:45:51,052 --> 01:45:53,214
I shall be getting drunk.

1407
01:45:53,732 --> 01:45:56,463
It's wonderful, an
absolute dream...

1408
01:46:09,690 --> 01:46:11,360
Are you okay?

1409
01:46:13,400 --> 01:46:14,990
Fine.

1410
01:46:16,610 --> 01:46:18,360
No regrets.

1411
01:46:21,620 --> 01:46:23,450
Not one.

1412
01:46:43,452 --> 01:46:45,454
And our special guest,

1413
01:46:45,532 --> 01:46:47,375
Formula 1 champion James Hunt.

1414
01:47:10,772 --> 01:47:12,854
Wait. Come on.

1415
01:47:16,012 --> 01:47:17,502
There's no better motor oil

1416
01:47:17,572 --> 01:47:19,176
than Havoline.

1417
01:47:29,692 --> 01:47:31,615
Yes, me, too. Where are we going?

1418
01:47:31,692 --> 01:47:33,182
Anywhere I want to go.

1419
01:47:33,252 --> 01:47:35,533
And I don't have to
hijack it, either.

1420
01:47:35,572 --> 01:47:37,222
As long as I pay for it.

1421
01:47:37,292 --> 01:47:39,613
I'm starving. Let's get some food.

1422
01:47:50,732 --> 01:47:52,461
- Where are we going?
- You lot go ahead.

1423
01:47:52,532 --> 01:47:54,500
I won't be a minute.

1424
01:48:00,412 --> 01:48:02,016
Good to see you.

1425
01:48:06,092 --> 01:48:08,493
I heard you were spending more
and more time in one of these.

1426
01:48:08,892 --> 01:48:10,860
- Do you fly?
- No.

1427
01:48:11,252 --> 01:48:12,742
I don't think they'd insure me.

1428
01:48:12,892 --> 01:48:14,735
You should try. It's
good for discipline.

1429
01:48:14,932 --> 01:48:17,412
You have to stay within the
rules, stick to regulations,

1430
01:48:17,532 --> 01:48:20,103
suppress the ego. It
helps with the racing.

1431
01:48:20,212 --> 01:48:23,182
And there I was thinking you
were about to wax lyrical

1432
01:48:23,252 --> 01:48:24,856
about the romance of flight.

1433
01:48:25,212 --> 01:48:26,782
No, that's all bullshit.

1434
01:48:27,932 --> 01:48:29,377
So, what brings you here?

1435
01:48:30,532 --> 01:48:33,012
A friend's wedding. At least
I think it was a wedding.

1436
01:48:33,092 --> 01:48:34,323
Might have been a birthday or

1437
01:48:34,324 --> 01:48:35,936
something. It's all
a bit of a blur.

1438
01:48:36,012 --> 01:48:37,612
How about you? Have
you been at Fiorano?

1439
01:48:37,632 --> 01:48:38,632
Pre-season testing.

1440
01:48:38,633 --> 01:48:40,535
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1441
01:48:40,612 --> 01:48:42,774
I'm not sure that was
meant as a compliment.

1442
01:48:42,852 --> 01:48:45,139
When do you start
testing? Next week?

1443
01:48:45,172 --> 01:48:47,140
No. What, are you nuts?

1444
01:48:47,212 --> 01:48:49,012
I didn't just win the
biggest thing of my life

1445
01:48:49,032 --> 01:48:50,477
so I could get right back to work.

1446
01:48:51,772 --> 01:48:54,457
Why? You have to.

1447
01:48:54,772 --> 01:48:56,410
To prove to all the
people who will

1448
01:48:56,411 --> 01:48:58,140
always say you just
won it because...

1449
01:48:58,212 --> 01:49:01,614
Because of what? Because
of your accident?

1450
01:49:03,132 --> 01:49:05,180
Niki, is that other
people, or is that you?

1451
01:49:05,812 --> 01:49:08,895
I won, okay? On the all-important
day, when it came down to it,

1452
01:49:08,972 --> 01:49:11,816
we raced on equal terms,
equally good cars.

1453
01:49:11,892 --> 01:49:14,054
And I put my life on the
line, and I saw it through.

1454
01:49:14,132 --> 01:49:16,180
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1455
01:49:16,292 --> 01:49:18,374
The risks were totally
unacceptable.

1456
01:49:18,892 --> 01:49:21,372
You were prepared to die.
To me, that's losing.

1457
01:49:21,492 --> 01:49:23,062
Yes, I was. I admit it.

1458
01:49:23,132 --> 01:49:25,976
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1459
01:49:26,012 --> 01:49:28,982
And that's the effect you have
on me. You'd pushed me that far.

1460
01:49:29,092 --> 01:49:30,503
And it felt great.

1461
01:49:31,412 --> 01:49:33,733
I mean, hell, isn't that
what we're in this for?

1462
01:49:33,812 --> 01:49:37,180
To stare death in the
face and to cheat it?

1463
01:49:37,532 --> 01:49:41,332
Come on, there's nobility in
that. It's like being knights.

1464
01:49:42,332 --> 01:49:44,096
You English, you're such assholes.

1465
01:49:45,052 --> 01:49:46,497
You know my position.

1466
01:49:46,772 --> 01:49:48,183
Twenty per cent risk.

1467
01:49:48,252 --> 01:49:49,954
No, no, no, Niki, don't bring the

1468
01:49:49,955 --> 01:49:52,018
percentages into this.
Don't be a pro.

1469
01:49:52,052 --> 01:49:54,703
The minute you do that, you
kill what's good about this.

1470
01:49:55,012 --> 01:49:56,776
You kill the sport.

1471
01:49:59,892 --> 01:50:01,542
James.

1472
01:50:01,852 --> 01:50:03,695
- James.
- Come on.

1473
01:50:06,692 --> 01:50:08,057
I've got to go.

1474
01:50:09,572 --> 01:50:11,540
Careful in this thing.

1475
01:50:12,572 --> 01:50:14,062
James.

1476
01:50:19,292 --> 01:50:21,149
You know, in hospital,
the toughest

1477
01:50:21,150 --> 01:50:23,058
part of my treatment
was the vacuum.

1478
01:50:23,372 --> 01:50:26,296
Pumping the shit out of
my lungs. It was hell.

1479
01:50:27,372 --> 01:50:29,295
And while doing it, I was
watching television.

1480
01:50:29,892 --> 01:50:32,657
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1481
01:50:32,732 --> 01:50:34,939
That bastard Hunt, I would
say. I hate that guy.

1482
01:50:35,492 --> 01:50:37,574
And then one day the
doctor came and said,

1483
01:50:37,652 --> 01:50:39,939
Mr Lauda, may I offer
a piece of advice?

1484
01:50:40,052 --> 01:50:43,738
Stop thinking of it as a curse to
have been given an enemy in life.

1485
01:50:43,812 --> 01:50:45,974
It can be a blessing, too.

1486
01:50:46,052 --> 01:50:47,597
A wise man gets more
from his enemies

1487
01:50:47,598 --> 01:50:48,817
than a fool from his friends.

1488
01:50:49,452 --> 01:50:51,739
And you know what? He was right.

1489
01:50:54,332 --> 01:50:58,098
Look at us. We were both a
pair of kids when we met.

1490
01:50:58,132 --> 01:50:59,941
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1491
01:50:59,972 --> 01:51:01,815
Disowned by our families.

1492
01:51:01,932 --> 01:51:03,297
Headed nowhere.

1493
01:51:04,412 --> 01:51:06,699
And now we're both
champions of the world.

1494
01:51:06,772 --> 01:51:08,183
It was not bad, huh?

1495
01:51:09,252 --> 01:51:11,175
No, it's not bad.

1496
01:51:11,252 --> 01:51:14,813
So, don't let me down now. I
need you busting my balls.

1497
01:51:15,252 --> 01:51:18,017
- Get back to work.
- I will, Niki, I will.

1498
01:51:18,772 --> 01:51:20,820
But I intend to
enjoy myself first.

1499
01:51:21,172 --> 01:51:23,493
Some of life needs
to be for pleasure.

1500
01:51:23,612 --> 01:51:26,934
What's the point of having a
million cups and medals and planes

1501
01:51:27,012 --> 01:51:29,174
if you don't have any fun?

1502
01:51:29,972 --> 01:51:31,701
How is that winning?

1503
01:51:32,772 --> 01:51:35,503
- James.
- We're gonna leave without you.

1504
01:51:36,012 --> 01:51:37,457
James.

1505
01:51:41,292 --> 01:51:42,703
I'll see you on race day, champ.

1506
01:51:44,452 --> 01:51:46,614
You will... champ.

1507
01:51:49,132 --> 01:51:50,896
You look good, Niki.

1508
01:51:51,452 --> 01:51:53,028
The only guy to
have his face burnt

1509
01:51:53,029 --> 01:51:54,342
off and it be an improvement.

1510
01:52:01,172 --> 01:52:03,220
Of course, he didn't listen to me.

1511
01:52:03,292 --> 01:52:04,737
For James,

1512
01:52:04,812 --> 01:52:06,974
one world title was enough.

1513
01:52:07,012 --> 01:52:08,502
He had proved

1514
01:52:08,532 --> 01:52:11,820
what he needed to
prove, to himself

1515
01:52:11,892 --> 01:52:14,179
and anyone who doubted him.

1516
01:52:15,012 --> 01:52:16,901
And two years later he retired.

1517
01:52:17,172 --> 01:52:20,813
When I saw him next in
London seven years later,

1518
01:52:20,932 --> 01:52:23,060
me as champion again,

1519
01:52:23,172 --> 01:52:25,061
him as broadcaster,

1520
01:52:25,132 --> 01:52:29,535
he was barefoot on a
bicycle with a flat tyre.

1521
01:52:29,652 --> 01:52:32,496
Still living each
day like his last.

1522
01:52:34,252 --> 01:52:35,742
When I heard he'd died,

1523
01:52:35,852 --> 01:52:38,219
aged 45, of a heart attack,

1524
01:52:38,332 --> 01:52:39,857
I wasn't surprised.

1525
01:52:40,852 --> 01:52:42,741
I was just sad.

1526
01:52:44,092 --> 01:52:45,935
People always think
of us as rivals,

1527
01:52:46,012 --> 01:52:49,619
but he was among the
very few I liked,

1528
01:52:50,932 --> 01:52:53,902
and even fewer that I respected.

1529
01:52:57,052 --> 01:52:59,783
He remains the only
person I envied.
